	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=32254><span id= >Nixoh</span></a><br><span id=notbold>484 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.74]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>One thing that a lot of people may not realize is that BA4 isn't all that much more useful to a necro than BA3, especially once you get yourself Funeral Pyre. Sure, it will help with you with your level 62 lifetap dot, but other than that it doesn't get you a whole lot. Your level 65 dot is only a bit better than FP, isn't affected by BA3 items, and has -50 resist (vs -100 on FP).<br><br>Personally, I would probably wield this until level 64 and and might even keep in on after dinging 65 (swapping in a mage-summoned item for boss fights where the little extra &quot;oomph&quot; from BoT would be most useful, and/or where I would actually use both).<br><br>But take a look at what else this item will do for you:<br><br>1. Ups the dmg on Splurt (finally, now that they've fixed it) for low-agro solo pulls with high eventual damage.<br><br>2. Ups the damage on Vexing Mordina, a MUST for long fights, and cheaper than the upgrade at 62.<br><br>3. Ups the damage on ebolt, which is a nice spell for those times that you're going to follow up with a lifetap nuke, thus shortening the fight to a point that FP would not be efficient.<br><br>I'll be grabbing this item when it drops (necros should all be hunting Takish first anyway for the pet focus AP item), and trust me, it won't be sold any time soon ;-)<br></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>You gain experience!<br>The Goblin Warlord hits YOU for 50 points!<br></td></tr>
